intro: Seseli wannienchun, commonly known as the Wannienchun seseli, is a flowering plant belonging to the Apiaceae family. It is characterized by its slender, branched stems and small, greenish-white flowers arranged in umbels. The plant typically grows in rocky or gravelly habitats, often in mountainous regions. Its leaves are finely divided and aromatic, similar to other members of its family. Seseli wannienchun is native to specific regions in China and is of interest to botanists due to its unique ecological adaptations.
